ame until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":10,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":19,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":54,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Dacre was born about 1205, in Dacre, Cumberland, England, his father, Ralph Dacre, was 27 and his mother, Joan Ros, was 22. He married Joan Morley in 1245, in Cumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1268, in his hometown, at the age of 64."},"et":{"Abt 1205–1268":"umbes 1205–1268","1205–1268":"1205–1268","1221–1280":"1221–1280","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1246–1286":"1246–1286","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1185–Female":"1185–Surnud","Abt 1205":"umbes 1205","1286":"1286","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1280":"1280","1180":"1180","1205":"1205","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1268":"1268","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","1245":"1245","1221":"1221","about 1246":